The House Committee on Governmental Affairs offers the following substitute to HB 414:
A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Chapter 5 of Title 21 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to
2 government transparency and campaign finance, so as to revise the definition of "person" to
3 include certain nonresidents of the state; to provide the State Ethics Commission with
4 supplementary investigatory powers related to persons, documents, or information located
5 outside of the state; to revise venue provisions to address out-of-state persons; to provide for
6 related matters; to repeal conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
7 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
8 SECTION 1.
9 Chapter 5 of Title 21 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to government
10 transparency and campaign finance, is amended in Code Section 21-5-3, relating to
11 definitions, by revising paragraph (19) as follows:
12 "(19) 'Person' means an individual, partnership, committee, association, corporation,
13 limited liability company, limited liability partnership, trust, professional corporation, or
14 other business entity recognized in the State of Georgia, labor organization, or any other
15 organization or group of persons, and shall include a 'nonresident' as that term is defined
